<chapter id="distro-2dxl">
 <title>2-Disk xwindow Linux</title>

<para>
Overview

   The distribution is intended to give a fully expandable X system
   implementation that can execute standard X applications, no special
   compilation required just dropin any libc2.1/X11R6 binary and it
   should run.

   The source tree is compiled on debian and the /lib/ files taken
   directly from the debian-2.2.3 distribution.

   The idea behind the distribution is to give users the minimum tools
   required for a unix system, because "THE SMALLER THE SYSTEM, THE
   SIMPLER THE ADMINISTRATION"

   The distribution is not specifically meant for:
     * corporate users to reuse old PC's as X terminals (running X on any
       thing less than a 486dx is not advisable)
       Or:
     * using as an embedded OS for handhelds or settop boxes
       Or:
     * using as a system rescue disk

   But it is probably the best basis for any of those functions and
   Mungkie Associates can consult and advise on implementation of your
   specific requirements.
</para>

<para>
Features

   The 2-disk xwindow distro is now in its first stable release, It's
   based on standard GNU/Linux components, mostly compiled without any
   modification. A fairly large amount of reimplementation has been
   enforced on some components (listed in brackets).

   kernel 2.4.12/libc-2.1, umsdos/ext2/initrd, network support. busybox,
   tinylogin, e3, Xwindows 4.1 vesa, (mouse and mode hack added) ppp,
   alloywm, chimera, (frames, applet swallow, added) xpaint, (command
   line exec, size reduction) xfm, (xpms edited, some minor hacking)
   xedit, some daemons, inetd, crond. dhcp client and server. iptables
   boots from umsdos, 

   boot from disk then run the Install2dos script to setup on you dos
   partition ( Beware this is untested and may damage your dos disk if
   you do not give the correct options).
   reboot to dos or windows, run c:\linux\linux.pif or c:\linux\linux.bat
</para>

<para>
Requirements:

   The system requires a minimum 486DX with 32Mb memory and a floppy disk
   drive.
</para>

<para>
Websted: http://www.thepub.nildram.co.uk/mirrors/2diskxwin/2diskXwin.htm
</para>

